message: The language is called Serbo-Croatian. Bosnian is just one of the four standardized registers of the Eastern Hercegovinian dialect of the Neo-Shtokavian variant of Serbo-Croatian, the others being Serbian, Croatian and Montenegrin. They're almost identical, save for some slight differences here and there.
